               <msContents>
                  <summary change="#add-summary">
                     1 copy of Kashf alʿallām fī tafsīr al-manām by Shams al-Dīn Muḥammad al-ʿUmarī
                  </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Islamic_Arabic_429-item1">
                     <author key="person_f3809">
                        <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied">Shams al-Dīn Muḥammad al-ʿUmarī</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" key="work_7645">Kashf alʿallām fī tafsīr al-manām</title>
                     <note>The text concludes with a 'tammat' and the date <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari" when="1447">581</date>, but it is impossible to say whether this refers to composition or copying; on the page facing the end of the work is what purports to be an owner's note dated <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari" when="1605">1014</date>. Both these indications, however, if they are not outright forgeries, must be reproduced from an earlier MS., for the paper of the present MS which is very thin and in various colours (bright blue, yellow, and pink) has a thoroughly modern appearance and can hardly be older than the <date calendar="#Gregorian" notBefore="1801" notAfter="1900">Gregorian</date> 19th century.</note>
                     <incipit xml:lang="ar">الحمد الله نور الباب من الانام و كشف عن بصائرهم حتى ادركوا حقيقه كل ما شاهدوه في اليقظة و المنام</incipit>
